      • saveToFile

        public SyncedDataKey.Builder<T> saveToFile()
        Saves this synced key to the players file. This means that the data will persist even if the player reloads a world or joins back into the server.

      • resetOnDeath

        public SyncedDataKey.Builder<T> resetOnDeath()
        Stops this synced key from transferring over when a player dies and basically resets the data back to the result of the default value supplier.

      • doNotSync

        public SyncedDataKey.Builder<T> doNotSync()
        Stops the synced key from syncing at all. This is only useful if the data only needs to be available on the server. This does contradict the whole idea of this system but creates a quick way to store data that is bound to a player.

      • restrictSync

        public SyncedDataKey.Builder<T> restrictSync()
        Restricts this synced key from syncing to everyone who is tracking the player and only to the player which data was changed.
